1
00:00:02,700 --> 00:00:04,500
Winter, 2007 in Japan,...

2
00:00:05,567 --> 00:00:09,600
various employment types
including the lifelong employment

3
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:11,767
and seniority system

4
00:00:11,934 --> 00:00:14,166
fell into a decline.

5
00:00:14,266 --> 00:00:15,633
"Economic bubble burst, 1991"

6
00:00:15,734 --> 00:00:19,133
After a long recession,
in an attempt to scale down,

7
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:22,233
it became common for companies
to seek to outsource.

8
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:25,066
As a result, the number
of non-regular employees,

9
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:30,100
particularly of temp workers,
saw explosive growth.

10
00:00:30,934 --> 00:00:34,200
There are currently three million
temp workers in Japan.

11
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,367
"Lowest employment rate
for college graduates, 2000"

12
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:38,033
Temp workers are paid hourly
without a bonus

13
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:40,567
and with no transportation
expenses included.

14
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,467
Their contract is reviewed
every three months.

15
00:00:43,734 --> 00:00:46,500
It's an unstable and harsh
working environment.

16
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:47,467
"Temp staffing industry
reached four trillion yen, 2005"

17
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:50,367
Still, temp workers brave
this difficult path.

18
00:00:54,166 --> 00:00:56,967
"Andalusia, Spain"

19
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:10,233
[Foreign language]

20
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:12,033
[Foreign language]

21
00:01:15,734 --> 00:01:16,800
Haruko?

22
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:18,567
I hear a strange sound.

23
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:20,166
Bring it to me.

24
00:01:20,266 --> 00:01:21,667
For example, this woman.

25
00:01:22,066 --> 00:01:26,000
Perhaps one day, suddenly,
the desk next to you at your company

26
00:01:26,266 --> 00:01:29,734
will be occupied by
a super temp worker like her.

27
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,900
So it's the next year now.

28
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:37,467
Haruko?

29
00:01:39,734 --> 00:01:42,066
I've got to go now.

30
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:45,734
Adios.

31
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:49,567
Adios.

32
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,400
"Tokyo"

33
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:04,700
Hello, Mum?

34
00:02:04,934 --> 00:02:06,333
"Miyuki Mori, 23, part time worker,
income: 810,000 yen"

35
00:02:06,433 --> 00:02:07,767
About the New Years...

36
00:02:08,066 --> 00:02:09,700
Sorry, I couldn't come home.

37
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:13,900
Don't worry about that.

38
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:18,600
I'll try to make it work
in Tokyo a little longer.

39
00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:23,600
There are so many companies
out here.

40
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:26,567
I'm sure I'll find a job somewhere.

41
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,667
Don't worry.

42
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:31,567
I'll go now.

43
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:32,867
Bye.

44
00:02:49,734 --> 00:02:50,734
Hi there.

45
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:53,166
"Personal information entry sheet"

46
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,000
"Education: Literature degree"

47
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,433
Work experience?

48
00:02:59,433 --> 00:03:00,333
I've got zero.

49
00:03:01,467 --> 00:03:02,734
Are you new to this?

50
00:03:03,166 --> 00:03:04,033
Yes.

51
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,834
We welcome people like you.

52
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:07,600
A temp worker...

53
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,166
signs up to an agency like us...

54
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:13,433
and sent to work
at various companies.

55
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
You'll be paid hourly
by our agency.

56
00:03:17,367 --> 00:03:18,200
Okay.

57
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,900
To sign up to our agency,

58
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:23,233
you'll be tested for common
knowledge and PC skills.

59
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:24,333
Well...

60
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:26,500
Don't worry, it's a very easy test.

61
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:29,967
Oh sorry, my name is Hitotsugi,
the manager.

62
00:03:30,066 --> 00:03:31,066
"Shinya Hitotsugi, 30 Haken Life
employee, income:4.02 million yen"

63
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:32,900
Feel free to ask me anything.

64
00:03:33,834 --> 00:03:37,834
I don't have high expectations.
I just need to find a job quickly.

65
00:03:45,033 --> 00:03:45,867
Yes!

66
00:03:46,467 --> 00:03:48,834
"First work day of
the year ceremony"

67
00:03:49,066 --> 00:03:50,967
Happy New Year.

68
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:54,400
There you go.

69
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,266
"Toshiro Kirishima, 54 S&amp;F director,
income: 16 million yen"

70
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:58,200
Hey.

71
00:03:58,433 --> 00:03:59,867
Use your hips more.

72
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:02,834
Sorry, I'm afraid that I will
hit your hand.

73
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:07,734
At this rate, the New Year's will
end before we eat pounded rice.

74
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:09,633
There you go!

75
00:04:09,734 --> 00:04:11,433
"Takeshi Shoji, S&amp;F employee
Income: 625,000 yen"

76
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,433
Director Kirishima.

77
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:13,333
Here I come.

78
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,266
There.

79
00:04:15,367 --> 00:04:16,200
Yeah.

80
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,333
Yeah!

81
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:18,266
What?

82
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:19,367
I like you.

83
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:20,400
Shut up.

84
00:04:21,033 --> 00:04:22,400
I'll follow you.

85
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:24,266
Make me your son.

86
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:25,333
No thanks.

87
00:04:25,433 --> 00:04:26,600
I'll follow you forever.

88
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:27,767
Stop talking.

89
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:28,800
Director...

90
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:30,000
"The Sales Division"

91
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:35,433
Kurumi?

92
00:04:37,834 --> 00:04:38,734
Isn't it good?

93
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:41,500
I did 80 percent of the work.

94
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:43,233
Okay, thanks.

95
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:44,166
Hey, Shoji.

96
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:46,100
Satonaka. Follow me.

97
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:48,867
An appointment.

98
00:04:50,567 --> 00:04:51,700
Hey, wait!

99
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,500
Takeshi Shoji, you're appointed
as Chief of Sales Section 2.

100
00:04:56,734 --> 00:04:57,567
Thank you.

101
00:04:58,100 --> 00:04:59,533
I'll give it all I have.

102
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,000
Thank you.

103
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,367
Congratulations.

104
00:05:04,734 --> 00:05:06,166
Thank you, everyone.

105
00:05:06,266 --> 00:05:07,867
Congratulations, Shoji.

106
00:05:08,233 --> 00:05:09,533
Thank you, Ken.

107
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:10,867
Kensuke Satonaka.

108
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:12,066
Yes.

109
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:14,934
You're now the chief
of Marketing Section.

110
00:05:16,033 --> 00:05:16,867
Great.

111
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,300
Do we have such a section here?

112
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:23,200
We decided that it's time for our
division to focus on marketing.

113
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:24,834
It's a new team.

114
00:05:26,734 --> 00:05:29,367
Your office will be
in the current archives.

115
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,500
I'm counting on you.

116
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:34,066
I mean it.

117
00:05:35,934 --> 00:05:36,934
Really.

118
00:05:37,834 --> 00:05:38,834
Director Kirishima.

119
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,266
If you emphasise that too much...

120
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,033
Thank you.

121
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:46,033
I'll do my best to meet
your expectations.

122
00:05:46,934 --> 00:05:47,767
Ken.

123
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,500
Marketing Section, huh?

124
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,900
I'm sorry, go ahead.

125
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,600
It's fine, I'm getting off.

126
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,200
Thank you.

127
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:30,233
What?

128
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:31,934
Nothing.

129
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,233
What?

130
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:39,000
Nothing.

131
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:48,900
"Word and Excel"

132
00:06:53,734 --> 00:06:56,867
Excuse, do you have any jobs
for me yet?

133
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:59,367
At this rate,
I'll lose my apartment.

134
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:00,700
We're doing our best.

135
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,533
However, since you have
no prior work experience,...

136
00:07:04,934 --> 00:07:07,166
your options are limited.

137
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:08,667
Please.

138
00:07:08,767 --> 00:07:10,000
- I'm begging you.
- Hold on.

139
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,166
Please hurry.

140
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:14,834
This is Hitotsugi.

141
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,066
Hi there.

142
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,033
How is it going?

143
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:19,333
What?

144
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,433
It's over?

145
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:23,834
Hold on a second.

146
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:27,767
They look down on us temp workers.

147
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,734
They only let us run errands.

148
00:07:29,934 --> 00:07:32,233
They made me go buy
their lunch yesterday.

149
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:34,100
That's not good.

150
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:36,567
Going to get people's lunches...

151
00:07:37,066 --> 00:07:38,600
shouldn't be your job.

152
00:07:38,834 --> 00:07:40,834
I'll talk to the person in charge.

153
00:07:40,934 --> 00:07:43,100
Please tell them that I'm quitting.

154
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:44,600
Ito?

155
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:48,900
Seriously?

156
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:51,767
She still has two months left.

157
00:07:52,934 --> 00:07:53,867
What about me?

158
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:56,533
I'd be happy to go buy lunch.

159
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:01,567
Director Kirishima.

160
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:04,133
Another temp worker just quit.

161
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,967
The agency is sending
a new person.

162
00:08:08,867 --> 00:08:10,567
So another interview?

163
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:14,066
Sir, it's a consultation,
not an interview.

164
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,233
Oh yeah?

165
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:16,400
A consultation?

166
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:18,967
It's different from an interview?

167
00:08:19,066 --> 00:08:20,100
Interviews...

168
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:23,133
are prohibited by
the Temporary Staffing Law.

169
00:08:23,367 --> 00:08:28,000
Companies are not supposed
to choose temp workers.

170
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:31,200
But they could still
turn me down, right?

171
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,700
Yes, very possible.

172
00:08:38,834 --> 00:08:40,700
It's basically the same thing.

173
00:08:40,867 --> 00:08:43,400
We just cannot call it
a job interview.

174
00:08:43,834 --> 00:08:46,000
I previously worked in HR.

175
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,100
Ask me anything
about outsourcing.

176
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:49,867
Enough with bragging.

177
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,333
Come with me.

178
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:54,033
Yes, I'll follow you until the end.

179
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:57,100
Satonaka.

180
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,433
You come, too.

181
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:02,433
She's just finished university,

182
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:04,834
so she doesn't have many skills.

183
00:09:05,033 --> 00:09:06,233
But she's a hard worker.

184
00:09:06,567 --> 00:09:07,500
Right?

185
00:09:07,834 --> 00:09:08,767
Yes.

186
00:09:08,934 --> 00:09:10,233
Can you use Word?

187
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,000
What? Sure.

188
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:13,467
Excel?

189
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:14,734
Yes.

190
00:09:15,033 --> 00:09:16,066
Power Point?

191
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:17,400
Yes, I can.

192
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,467
She can work right away, then.

193
00:09:20,567 --> 00:09:22,233
Yes, you can count on me.

194
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:25,433
By the way, you got
Haruko Omae, right?

195
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:28,600
Yes, we've got her.
Consultation is with her tomorrow.

196
00:09:28,867 --> 00:09:29,734
Okay.

197
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:32,333
Since Ms Omae will be back,...

198
00:09:33,066 --> 00:09:35,066
this lady can join us.

199
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,700
We have a new section.

200
00:09:37,867 --> 00:09:39,867
You'll join our Marketing Section.

201
00:09:41,066 --> 00:09:42,700
Great, I'll do my best.

202
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:45,600
I'm Chief Satonaka.

203
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:46,934
Great to have you.

204
00:09:47,066 --> 00:09:48,300
Thank you very much.

205
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,266
Sir.

206
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,233
Who's Haruko Omae?

207
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,100
"Marunouchi"

208
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,266
Sometimes you meet someone,...

209
00:10:24,734 --> 00:10:27,266
and you become
a completely different person.

210
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:31,100
Who is that person for me?

211
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:53,333
Haruko Omae gave a great impact...

212
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:55,700
on my life.

213
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:57,600
And...

214
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:01,266
she taught me something
very important.

215
00:11:04,734 --> 00:11:08,266
She taught me that
working is living.

216
00:11:14,467 --> 00:11:19,367
"The Pride of The Temp"

217
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:23,734
"A super temp worker makes
an appearance"

218
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:25,233
Really?

219
00:11:25,934 --> 00:11:27,100
Sorry for the wait.

220
00:11:28,433 --> 00:11:29,467
Some tea?

221
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,100
Great to see you.

222
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,066
Hi there.

223
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:37,200
We proudly present Haruko Omae,
a Special A Rank temp worker.

224
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:40,066
So this is her.

225
00:11:40,834 --> 00:11:41,900
Nice to meet you.

226
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:43,867
I'm Satonaka from Marketing.

227
00:11:47,266 --> 00:11:48,166
What's wrong?

228
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,533
Sit down.

229
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,667
I'm the Chief of Sales.

230
00:11:53,834 --> 00:11:56,734
But I'm here on behalf
of our director.

231
00:11:57,467 --> 00:12:00,900
Since you're a temp,
your job is assisting the chief...

232
00:12:01,266 --> 00:12:02,467
and running errands.

233
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,867
Where did you work before?

234
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,033
Was my voice too soft?

235
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,433
You heard it, right?

236
00:12:16,934 --> 00:12:18,266
Where were you before?

237
00:12:19,533 --> 00:12:21,166
Hello?

238
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:25,834
I'm not sure who's the one
doing consultation now.

239
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,033
I'll answer for her.

240
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,367
I'll explain the conditions.

241
00:12:31,734 --> 00:12:32,734
Conditions?

242
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,266
The contract is for three months.

243
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:41,433
Monday to Friday, 9:00 a.m. to 6:00
p.m. with one-hour lunch break.

244
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:43,967
Extension of contract
is not allowed.

245
00:12:44,734 --> 00:12:47,066
No work outside
of the assigned section.

246
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:50,100
No work on weekends
or overtime.

247
00:12:52,066 --> 00:12:52,900
That's all.

248
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,066
Wait a minute.

249
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,900
So many "Nos".

250
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,433
Why don't you say anything?

251
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:09,467
Even if you're a temp, we expect you
to do overtime if we're busy. Right?

252
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:11,834
Sure.

253
00:13:11,934 --> 00:13:14,567
It depends on the situation.

254
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:17,400
But basically this is how she works.

255
00:13:17,734 --> 00:13:18,900
That's it.

256
00:13:19,266 --> 00:13:23,467
Director Kirishima has requested
her to start working today.

257
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,900
Is Kirishima serious
about hiring her?

258
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:29,533
That's crazy.

259
00:13:30,734 --> 00:13:33,033
She doesn't even blink.
Is she alive?

260
00:13:34,934 --> 00:13:35,867
She moved.

261
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,333
Is this some kind of a joke?

262
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:42,767
What's with the attitude?
Say something.

263
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:48,200
This is terrible.

264
00:13:53,734 --> 00:13:55,867
You will not regret hiring me.

265
00:13:56,533 --> 00:14:00,500
I'll work hard for the three months
I'm being paid.

266
00:14:01,266 --> 00:14:02,700
Hourly wage?

267
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:09,767
- Here she comes.
- She's the one?

268
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:12,233
The Special A Rank temp worker.

269
00:14:13,467 --> 00:14:14,200
Hey.

270
00:14:14,767 --> 00:14:15,700
Well...

271
00:14:16,066 --> 00:14:18,333
Marketing Section's here.

272
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,934
Good morning, everyone.

273
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:24,166
Good morning.

274
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:27,467
I'm Miyuki Mori with Haken Life.

275
00:14:27,567 --> 00:14:29,433
Nice to meet you.

276
00:14:30,066 --> 00:14:31,967
I'm also new to this section.

277
00:14:32,066 --> 00:14:33,400
Let's do our best.

278
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:36,400
Please use this desk.

279
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,467
- Okay.
- Chief.

280
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:38,900
Is this everyone?

281
00:14:39,066 --> 00:14:41,066
Yes. Thank you, Asano.

282
00:14:41,266 --> 00:14:43,800
Just me, with one year's experience
and the temp workers.

283
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:45,600
What a scratch team.

284
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:46,900
That's not true.

285
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:48,800
We have an experienced member,
Ogasawara.

286
00:14:50,266 --> 00:14:51,233
Ogasawara.

287
00:14:51,567 --> 00:14:52,567
Glad to have you.

288
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:53,633
Thanks.

289
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,333
Nice to meet you.

290
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:58,700
Marketing Section
was recently created.

291
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:02,900
I'm not sure
where we should begin myself.

292
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:06,667
But let's work together
and build a good team.

293
00:15:07,934 --> 00:15:10,667
Can you give a word, too, Omae?

294
00:15:15,967 --> 00:15:17,533
I'll help you out.

295
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:21,333
You don't need to get
to work right away.

296
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:23,900
Get used to the office for today.

297
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,400
Omae, you don't
need to do anything yet.

298
00:15:43,066 --> 00:15:44,000
Hey.

299
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:46,133
Has she been like that?

300
00:15:48,066 --> 00:15:48,900
Yes.

301
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Well...

302
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,867
Did I upset you?

303
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:56,400
I'm just following the chief's order
to do nothing.

304
00:15:56,667 --> 00:15:57,500
Problem?

305
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,600
Oh, I see.

306
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,934
Here's your ID.

307
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:06,567
You seem to have a lot of free time.

308
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,767
Can you help me out with this, Temp?

309
00:16:11,667 --> 00:16:12,600
What?

310
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,066
What's up with her?

311
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:16,400
It's her first day.

312
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,467
Hey.

313
00:16:18,166 --> 00:16:19,000
Hey.

314
00:16:20,734 --> 00:16:22,633
We're paying you, so work.

315
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,000
Not like that, Shoji.

316
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:25,767
First impression is the key.

317
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,500
Or she'll underestimate us.

318
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:37,100
Chief, this crazy curly hair
is not my boss.

319
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:41,967
Crazy curly hair?

320
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,800
Nobody says that.

321
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:45,800
I see.

322
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,700
You ignore everyone else?

323
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:48,967
- Yes.
- Kidding me?

324
00:16:49,066 --> 00:16:51,000
My name is Haruko Omae.

325
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:56,400
She's useless.

326
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,633
Never mind.

327
00:16:58,734 --> 00:16:59,667
Sorry.

328
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:00,734
It's not you.

329
00:17:00,834 --> 00:17:02,000
- Yeah.
- Hey.

330
00:17:02,166 --> 00:17:03,800
I'd be happy to do it.

331
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:06,500
Oh yeah, we have her.

332
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,000
- You're Mori, right?
- Yes.

333
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:09,400
- Good with computers, right?
- What?

334
00:17:09,934 --> 00:17:11,166
Yes, I am.

335
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:14,066
This is the revenue by region.

336
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,100
Compile them by product.

337
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,066
With sales offices and branches.

338
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:20,066
Sure.

339
00:17:20,166 --> 00:17:21,200
Right away.

340
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:23,600
Take your time, do it roughly.

341
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:25,100
Okay.

342
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:28,100
Darn.

343
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,266
For you, Omae...

344
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,200
Can you make us some tea?

345
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:38,967
It's noon, so see you later.

346
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:43,600
Hey.

347
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:45,567
Again.

348
00:17:45,767 --> 00:17:47,133
She looked at my hair.

349
00:17:47,934 --> 00:17:50,367
Watch out for Chief Shoji.

350
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:53,734
He's good at his job, but
he doesn't like temp workers.

351
00:17:53,834 --> 00:17:56,767
He doesn't hesitate to fire ones
he doesn't like.

352
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:07,967
Nice.

353
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,567
What are you looking at?

354
00:18:11,233 --> 00:18:12,467
It appears that...

355
00:18:12,834 --> 00:18:14,467
they're talking about us.

356
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:16,900
Enough.

357
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,066
Don't get attached to a temp.

358
00:18:20,066 --> 00:18:21,233
This is a secret,

359
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:23,433
but our director's wife was a temp.

360
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:25,500
That's rough.

361
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:30,000
So was it not her?

362
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:36,934
Wait.

363
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,633
No, it has to be her.

364
00:18:41,066 --> 00:18:42,300
Are you okay, Ken?

365
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,100
What should I do?

366
00:18:48,166 --> 00:18:49,433
That temp.

367
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,567
She's the worst
of all the ones I've seen.

368
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,700
But Kirishima wanted her?

369
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:55,667
Yes.

370
00:18:56,433 --> 00:18:59,467
Maybe she's blackmailing
the director.

371
00:18:59,567 --> 00:19:01,667
- Oh.
- What do you mean?

372
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:04,467
You guys have a great imagination.

373
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,233
Sir...

374
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:10,533
Don't be stupid. No one can ever
blackmail our director.

375
00:19:10,934 --> 00:19:12,967
Are you done eating?

376
00:19:13,667 --> 00:19:15,000
I'll clean it for you.

377
00:19:16,066 --> 00:19:17,000
Sorry.

378
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:20,567
Satonaka?

379
00:19:20,734 --> 00:19:21,567
Yes.

380
00:19:21,667 --> 00:19:24,767
Do a market research on rice
before next Wednesday.

381
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:26,900
Sure.

382
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,133
First task for
the Marketing Section.

383
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,900
You'll present it
at the product meeting.

384
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:33,500
Okay.

385
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,467
Work hard...

386
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:36,433
and get good results.

387
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,600
Yes, I'll do my best.

388
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,467
Thank you.

389
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:44,266
Welcome.

390
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,767
Please share the table.

391
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:50,900
Hi there.

392
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,500
That looks good.

393
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,633
Same thing for me, please.

394
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,266
Brown or white rice?

395
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:01,600
White rice.

396
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:05,233
Here you go.

397
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Excuse me.

398
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:11,066
Wait.

399
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:12,467
Yes?

400
00:20:12,567 --> 00:20:14,567
- One person.
- I'll get this.

401
00:20:15,433 --> 00:20:16,233
No thanks.

402
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:17,400
But...

403
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:21,000
I'm retired and now I work
as a part-time worker...

404
00:20:21,433 --> 00:20:25,333
but I still make enough to buy
a temp worker lunch.

405
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:26,500
No, thank you.

406
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:29,500
Accept other people's kindness.

407
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,667
- No, thank you.
- You're stubborn.

408
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,867
I don't want to sound patronising,

409
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:40,834
but I know that life isn't easy
with your low-paying job.

410
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:44,834
After lunch and transportation,
not much would be left.

411
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:47,633
Please don't worry about it.

412
00:20:52,166 --> 00:20:56,066
What are you trying to prove,
you poor temp worker?

413
00:21:08,734 --> 00:21:10,800
We'll present this next Wednesday.

414
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:12,934
We need to research first.

415
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:15,967
Where's Omae?

416
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:20,433
That's thoughtful.

417
00:21:20,934 --> 00:21:21,734
Thanks.

418
00:21:21,834 --> 00:21:24,233
You asked me to make tea
before lunch.

419
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,567
Oh yeah, that's right.

420
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:29,433
For me, too? Thank you.

421
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:35,600
Is this new tea?

422
00:21:35,734 --> 00:21:39,300
No, it's the same tea I found
in the kitchen.

423
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,500
It's very good.

424
00:21:44,266 --> 00:21:46,166
Worth paying 3,000 yen per hour.

425
00:21:46,467 --> 00:21:47,400
What?

426
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:52,300
Someone from General Affairs told me
that she worked for them before.

427
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:54,266
Her rate is 3,000 yen per hour.

428
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:56,433
Three thousand yen?

429
00:21:57,967 --> 00:21:59,400
Are you okay?

430
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,700
Get a cloth.

431
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,433
It's so hot.

432
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,433
- Hot.
- Hold on.

433
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,467
Hot.

434
00:22:06,834 --> 00:22:08,300
"To understand what kind of
rice dishes are eaten..."

435
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:10,867
"New products"

436
00:22:12,934 --> 00:22:13,967
Omae?

437
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:15,233
Well...

438
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:17,533
It's done.

439
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,633
What?

440
00:22:22,734 --> 00:22:23,567
What?

441
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:28,567
What's this?

442
00:22:30,266 --> 00:22:31,000
Look at that.

443
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:32,333
"Presentation strategy"

444
00:22:32,433 --> 00:22:33,567
I see my name in it.

445
00:22:34,133 --> 00:22:35,266
What should I do?

446
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,367
You'll sort internal references.

447
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:39,867
Okay.

448
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,000
Ms. Temp?

449
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,000
Are you finished?

450
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:45,033
Sorry, I'm not done yet.

451
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:48,500
But it's been hours.

452
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:52,133
What? It's so sloppy.

453
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:55,066
I can't use this.

454
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:59,000
You mentioned that you can use
Excel and Power Point.

455
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:01,033
Sorry.

456
00:23:01,133 --> 00:23:03,700
Sorry? Is that all you can say?

457
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:04,700
Did you lie?

458
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:07,200
No, right?

459
00:23:07,467 --> 00:23:08,800
You didn't, did you?

460
00:23:11,066 --> 00:23:13,066
This is unacceptable.

461
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,900
That's not a proper way
of communicating.

462
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:18,000
What?

463
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:20,467
Who are you talking to?

464
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:24,734
Earlier, you told her not to rush
and do it roughly.

465
00:23:24,834 --> 00:23:26,300
So what?

466
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:29,500
You told her it's okay to take hours
and make it sloppy.

467
00:23:30,333 --> 00:23:33,834
No, I would never be okay
with that.

468
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:35,333
What's with you?

469
00:23:35,433 --> 00:23:36,567
That's all.

470
00:23:39,700 --> 00:23:41,233
Do it all over again.

471
00:23:41,834 --> 00:23:42,667
Okay.

472
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:45,834
Prove that you weren't lying
or you'll be in trouble.

473
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,066
Can you help me out, Asano?

474
00:23:51,166 --> 00:23:52,900
Let's take the trash out.

475
00:23:54,834 --> 00:23:55,834
Oh yeah!

476
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:57,767
We should do a welcome dinner.

477
00:23:58,433 --> 00:23:59,567
All of us.

478
00:23:59,667 --> 00:24:01,633
That sounds good.

479
00:24:01,734 --> 00:24:03,967
You should come too, Omae.

480
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:08,600
I'll leave office on time.

481
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,233
Please sign this for approval.

482
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:27,700
What do you think of your team?

483
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:31,000
You might find the members
not very capable.

484
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:32,000
You're right.

485
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,500
What?

486
00:24:33,667 --> 00:24:36,834
If you need help, I can
possibly add more employees.

487
00:24:37,233 --> 00:24:39,333
No, thank you. They're useless.

488
00:24:41,900 --> 00:24:42,834
What?

489
00:24:43,133 --> 00:24:44,333
If you're hiring,

490
00:24:44,433 --> 00:24:47,300
please add temp workers
with high computer skills.

491
00:24:47,734 --> 00:24:49,567
You don't have rights to decide.

492
00:24:50,133 --> 00:24:52,000
All right, I'll consider it.

493
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,266
- Thank you.
- What?

494
00:24:58,300 --> 00:24:59,166
Sir...

495
00:25:00,467 --> 00:25:01,600
That's unacceptable.

496
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:05,000
We use temp workers in order
to reduce labour costs.

497
00:25:06,266 --> 00:25:08,233
That's common sense.

498
00:25:09,233 --> 00:25:10,567
Just for three months.

499
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:25,400
You should get rid of her.

500
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:28,433
She's just not used to the job.
It's fine.

501
00:25:29,266 --> 00:25:31,633
Maybe Omae can help her out.

502
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,834
No way.

503
00:25:33,166 --> 00:25:36,600
She'll never help her out.

504
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:37,567
Why?

505
00:25:37,834 --> 00:25:42,033
She complained and asked
to hire someone who's more skilled.

506
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:43,567
She did?

507
00:25:43,667 --> 00:25:45,900
So the new temp girl
can be replaced.

508
00:25:50,734 --> 00:25:51,667
Manager.

509
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:53,200
The division policy.

510
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:54,400
Azukama, Sekiguchi,

511
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:56,166
- get quality evaluation done.
- Sure.

512
00:25:56,266 --> 00:25:59,133
Takahashi, let's have a meeting
when I get back.

513
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:00,600
Check this.

514
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:01,500
Shoji.

515
00:26:01,767 --> 00:26:03,400
You're busy now, right?

516
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:04,967
It's okay.

517
00:26:06,133 --> 00:26:08,000
You're in my way.

518
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,967
Hey, you temp!

519
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:14,166
Pick these up.

520
00:26:15,934 --> 00:26:20,000
I can't stand that woman!

521
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:21,433
Look at this.

522
00:26:21,734 --> 00:26:23,667
My hair is getting all curly!

523
00:26:24,266 --> 00:26:25,633
You look fine.

524
00:26:26,233 --> 00:26:27,233
You think so?

525
00:26:28,066 --> 00:26:30,233
You shouldn't be the one
picking them up.

526
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:32,800
But thanks.

527
00:26:34,934 --> 00:26:37,000
Sorry that I got upset.

528
00:26:38,667 --> 00:26:40,867
What's going on, Ken?

529
00:26:40,967 --> 00:26:41,900
Well...

530
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:46,433
My team doesn't seem to be together,
so I was thinking of having...

531
00:26:47,300 --> 00:26:48,400
a welcome dinner.

532
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,266
That sounds good.

533
00:26:50,767 --> 00:26:52,000
That's important.

534
00:26:52,633 --> 00:26:54,600
Everyone has to be there.

535
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:58,033
But Omae said she'll leave on time.

536
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:03,500
That's the biggest problem
that you have now?

537
00:27:04,066 --> 00:27:07,667
Pull yourself together or
she will have everything her way.

538
00:27:08,967 --> 00:27:11,333
But she is very competent.

539
00:27:11,734 --> 00:27:14,500
Still, she needs
to listen to her boss.

540
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:20,433
All right.

541
00:27:22,133 --> 00:27:23,600
I'll make it work.

542
00:27:24,166 --> 00:27:27,133
Hi. Thank you for
your continuous support.

543
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:29,967
Haruko Omae?

544
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:32,834
Satonaka, her boss,

545
00:27:32,934 --> 00:27:36,100
is at a loss
with how to handle her.

546
00:27:37,266 --> 00:27:38,867
Hitotsugi,...

547
00:27:39,266 --> 00:27:42,800
we may stop taking
temp workers from your agency.

548
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:44,934
Wait.

549
00:27:45,433 --> 00:27:46,500
What do you mean?

550
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,333
"Questionnaire on rice"

551
00:27:55,433 --> 00:27:57,800
"Please see the attached
questionnaire and..."

552
00:28:11,734 --> 00:28:13,500
The welcome dinner is tonight.

553
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:16,166
I've been looking forward to this.

554
00:28:16,300 --> 00:28:17,367
Where will we go?

555
00:28:17,467 --> 00:28:18,800
About that...

556
00:28:19,066 --> 00:28:20,734
- Omae...
- It's fine.

557
00:28:21,567 --> 00:28:23,600
I spoke with Hitotsugi.

558
00:28:24,133 --> 00:28:26,433
You love work dinners, don't you?

559
00:28:26,734 --> 00:28:28,066
Don't drink too much.

560
00:28:28,166 --> 00:28:29,266
Got it.

561
00:28:30,066 --> 00:28:30,967
Leave it to me.

