00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:36,800
Sorry?

843
00:49:36,900 --> 00:49:41,066
Still, people give everything
they have to the company.

844
00:49:42,433 --> 00:49:44,100
Is that...

845
00:49:44,200 --> 00:49:45,100
Waste of time.

846
00:49:46,500 --> 00:49:47,400
All of that.

847
00:49:51,066 --> 00:49:52,934
Even with a 100-year recession

848
00:49:53,033 --> 00:49:55,367
or an economic crisis,
I'll still survive.

849
00:49:57,600 --> 00:49:58,867
A temp should trust...

850
00:50:00,533 --> 00:50:02,100
only themselves and money.

851
00:50:03,867 --> 00:50:06,333
With techniques
and skills to survive,...

852
00:50:07,834 --> 00:50:09,834
you can live however you want.

853
00:50:12,500 --> 00:50:15,867
Are you by any chance trying
to cheer me up?

854
00:50:16,066 --> 00:50:17,166
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

855
00:50:17,266 --> 00:50:18,166
Tea, please.

856
00:50:21,667 --> 00:50:22,834
In any case,...

857
00:50:23,700 --> 00:50:27,033
thank you for coming
to my rescue earlier.

858
00:50:28,300 --> 00:50:29,834
I didn't come to your rescue.

859
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:32,934
It's part of my job.

860
00:50:35,533 --> 00:50:37,033
Besides, you're not safe.

861
00:50:37,834 --> 00:50:38,767
You'll be fired.

862
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:40,300
After today.

863
00:50:44,433 --> 00:50:46,934
You should never take work home.

864
00:50:49,166 --> 00:50:52,133
- Sorry.
- Apologising to me does nothing.

865
00:50:54,567 --> 00:50:55,767
I'm sorry.

866
00:51:03,934 --> 00:51:08,166
For the rest of the day,
work hard for your hourly wage.

867
00:51:10,667 --> 00:51:11,900
That's what I'd do.

868
00:51:14,867 --> 00:51:15,834
Thank you.

869
00:51:49,500 --> 00:51:50,567
Chief.

870
00:51:51,667 --> 00:51:53,600
Please give me another chance.

871
00:51:57,867 --> 00:52:01,433
Since we have the disk back,
I'll not report this to my boss.

872
00:52:03,433 --> 00:52:04,767
As a penalty,...

873
00:52:05,266 --> 00:52:06,700
do some unpaid overtime.

874
00:52:09,533 --> 00:52:10,400
Okay.

875
00:52:10,633 --> 00:52:11,600
Good luck.

876
00:52:19,033 --> 00:52:23,633
You looked quite impressive today.

877
00:52:23,734 --> 00:52:26,266
I had no idea
you had a crane licence.

878
00:52:26,367 --> 00:52:27,967
I didn't know, either.

879
00:52:28,066 --> 00:52:29,100
So what?

880
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:51,000
So you'll keep the temp?

881
00:52:53,834 --> 00:52:55,533
You're so easy on them.

882
00:52:56,700 --> 00:52:57,667
You're right.

883
00:53:00,900 --> 00:53:03,066
When we first joined the company,...

884
00:53:04,033 --> 00:53:07,000
the older lady told us
how to answer phone calls...

885
00:53:08,400 --> 00:53:11,100
and Chief Kawasaki often
treated us to dinner.

886
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:13,233
Remember that?

887
00:53:13,500 --> 00:53:14,367
Yeah.

888
00:53:15,834 --> 00:53:17,400
I wonder how they are now.

889
00:53:20,100 --> 00:53:22,100
Everyone got laid off.

890
00:53:23,667 --> 00:53:26,600
Now it's just temp workers
who are strangers to us.

891
00:53:30,433 --> 00:53:31,667
Can you accept that?

892
00:53:36,667 --> 00:53:37,567
For me,...

893
00:53:39,433 --> 00:53:42,166
I wanted to keep working with them.

894
00:53:44,300 --> 00:53:46,233
We shared meals together,...

895
00:53:46,867 --> 00:53:48,166
we cried and laughed,...

896
00:53:49,567 --> 00:53:50,767
like a family.

897
00:53:53,166 --> 00:53:55,700
I thought we'd be together forever.

898
00:53:58,667 --> 00:54:00,066
It doesn't make sense.

899
00:54:02,934 --> 00:54:05,100
It's like the space invaders game.

900
00:54:07,100 --> 00:54:08,233
Shoji.

901
00:54:09,166 --> 00:54:10,834
That makes you sound old.

902
00:54:14,100 --> 00:54:16,667
Don't get shot down, okay?

903
00:54:24,700 --> 00:54:25,700
Omae.

904
00:54:27,066 --> 00:54:28,533
- Good morning.
- Morning.

905
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:29,834
Morning.

906
00:54:30,233 --> 00:54:31,266
- Good morning.
- Morning.

907
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:34,600
With Mori's help,
we managed to finish.

908
00:54:34,934 --> 00:54:36,900
We stayed until 11:00 p.m.
last night.

909
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:40,467
How is it possible to spend
that many hours on that?

910
00:54:43,867 --> 00:54:46,200
I'll follow you forever, Omae.

911
00:54:58,567 --> 00:54:59,567
Good tea.

912
00:55:03,233 --> 00:55:05,200
We the Marketing Section...

913
00:55:05,567 --> 00:55:10,867
did our own market research
on processed rice products.

914
00:55:11,700 --> 00:55:15,133
We did a food service industry
research on restaurants...

915
00:55:27,300 --> 00:55:28,266
Nice work.

916
00:55:28,567 --> 00:55:29,567
I was so nervous.

917
00:55:29,667 --> 00:55:30,834
You did a good job.

918
00:55:31,100 --> 00:55:32,100
Satonaka.

919
00:55:32,400 --> 00:55:33,266
Yes.

920
00:55:33,367 --> 00:55:35,066
Good job for your first task.

921
00:55:35,266 --> 00:55:36,200
Thank you.

922
00:55:37,333 --> 00:55:41,233
I'll take you to
somewhere nice tonight.

923
00:55:43,233 --> 00:55:44,300
Thank you.

924
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:50,066
This way.

925
00:55:52,500 --> 00:55:53,767
Over here.

926
00:55:57,700 --> 00:55:58,934
Welcome.

927
00:56:00,467 --> 00:56:02,467
I thought we were going to a club.

928
00:56:02,567 --> 00:56:04,300
But flamenco? Really?

929
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:06,300
Ever been to a place like this?

930
00:56:06,400 --> 00:56:07,333
- No.
- Hey.

931
00:56:07,433 --> 00:56:08,533
Come sit down.

932
00:56:11,834 --> 00:56:15,934
I've always wanted to see flamenco.

933
00:56:16,033 --> 00:56:16,867
Thank you.

934
00:56:17,400 --> 00:56:20,533
Flamenco isn't for watching
but for listening.

935
00:56:20,900 --> 00:56:22,500
You know a lot about it.

936
00:57:11,266 --> 00:57:14,867
She makes fun of us
instead of making us look good.

937
00:57:15,200 --> 00:57:17,300
What's the pride of a temp?

938
00:57:17,400 --> 00:57:18,967
That's a stupid question.

939
00:57:19,200 --> 00:57:20,734
It's a stapler battle.

940
00:57:20,834 --> 00:57:23,266
What's more important than pride?

941
00:57:23,367 --> 00:57:28,367
"This drama series is a fiction"

